column5: I thought limey's was an alewife..?
Both pics are smelts. Alewife has a rounder body.
Maybe a cisco , but either way it would look good on a jig !
That second one is an Atlantic.
If it doesn't have an adipose fin, just before the tail, it's not a smelt. Can't tell from your pic.

Great point about the adipose. Could eliminate Smelt really easily if there is no adipose.  Another way of telling if the fish is alive and in hand - smell it. If it smells like cucumbers, Rainbow Smelt.  My guess would be Emerald Shiner.  Jon
Simcoe use to have alot that size. They called them rainbow smelt.
Actually  that last one looks alot more like a (salt-water) mulllet
